## 🗄️ Database Changes Needed

Your current database has **4 tables**: `products`, `orders`, `order_items`, `whatsapp_cart`.

To match WooCommerce, you would need approximately **15-20 additional tables**:

```sql
-- New tables needed:
customers              -- Customer accounts (email, password hash, profile)
customer_addresses     -- Multiple saved addresses per customer
shipping_zones         -- Geographic shipping zones
shipping_methods       -- Methods per zone (flat rate, free, express)
shipping_classes       -- Product shipping classes
tax_rates              -- Tax rates by state/country
tax_classes            -- Standard, Reduced, Zero-rate
coupons                -- Discount codes
coupon_usage           -- Track coupon usage per customer
product_reviews        -- Star ratings & text reviews
product_attributes     -- size, color, material, weight, dimensions
product_variants       -- SKU variants with separate stock/price
product_images         -- Multiple images per product
refunds                -- Refund records
transactions           -- Payment gateway transaction log
email_templates        -- Customizable notification templates
pages                  -- Privacy policy, Terms & Conditions, About
app_settings           -- Persist all settings (already partially exists)
```

---

> [!NOTE]
> **Your WhatsApp integration is a major competitive advantage** — WooCommerce requires expensive plugins (₹5,000-₹15,000/year) for similar WhatsApp functionality. Your built-in conversational commerce, broadcast messaging, and WhatsApp checkout flow are features that most WooCommerce stores don't have.

> [!TIP]
> **Recommended first steps**: Start with Phase 1 items #1 (settings persistence), #2 (Razorpay), #3 (GST tax), and #6 (persistent cart). These four changes alone will make a dramatic difference in your store's professionalism and legal compliance.
